#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17104
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//droneBlueprint[@name=\"FR_COMMONWEALTH_COMBAT_SURGE\"]/title"
msgstr "Overcharged Commonwealth Harbinger Drone Mk. II"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17105
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//droneBlueprint[@name=\"FR_COMMONWEALTH_COMBAT_SURGE\"]/short"
msgstr "O. ⛼ Harb. II"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17106
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//droneBlueprint[@name=\"FR_COMMONWEALTH_COMBAT_SURGE\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"A drone that precedes all known drone tech. Appears to be equipped with "
"Laser tech that does high damage. This overcharged version deals all types "
"of damage."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17122
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//weaponBlueprint[@name=\"FR_COMMONWEALTH_DRONE_SURGE\"]/title"
msgstr "Ancient Laser"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17123
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//weaponBlueprint[@name=\"FR_COMMONWEALTH_DRONE_SURGE\"]/short"
msgstr "A. Laser"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17125
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//weaponBlueprint[@name=\"FR_COMMONWEALTH_DRONE_SURGE\"]/desc"
msgstr "DRONE WEAPON"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17164
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//weaponBlueprint[@name=\"FISH_FOOD_FR_TARTARUS\"]/title"
msgstr "Undead Fish"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17165
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//weaponBlueprint[@name=\"FISH_FOOD_FR_TARTARUS\"]/short"
msgstr "Undead Fish"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17166
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//weaponBlueprint[@name=\"FISH_FOOD_FR_TARTARUS\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"An undead fish. When consumed, gives a +50% sabotage bonus and phasing to "
"all friendly crew."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17214
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_PERFECTED_SHIELD\"]/title"
msgstr "Perfected Shields"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17215
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_PERFECTED_SHIELD\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"Shields born from the perfected unity of every caste of Obelisk. It is stronger than the sum of its parts.\n"
"\t\n"
"\tHas an integrity of 20 hitpoints and grants +50% ion resistance."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17225
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_PERFECTED_PLATING\"]/title"
msgstr "Perfected Plating"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17226
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_PERFECTED_PLATING\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"Hull plating born from the perfected unity of every kind of Augmented. It is stronger than the sum of its parts.\n"
"\t\n"
"\tHas the effect of every arm and reduces crew's active ability cooldowns by 50%."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17236
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_PERFECTED_INTERNALS\"]/title"
msgstr "Perfected Internals"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17237
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_PERFECTED_INTERNALS\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"Internal components born from the perfected unity of every type of Cognitive. It is stronger than the sum of its parts.\n"
"\t\n"
"\tRepairs breaches, extinguishes fires, heals friendly metalloid crew for 5 hp/s and damages enemy metalloid crew and boarding drones for the same amount.\n"
"\t\n"
"\tMakes all crew controllable."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17249
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_COMMONWEALTH_SHIELD\"]/title"
msgstr "Ionic Shields"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17250
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_COMMONWEALTH_SHIELD\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"The Commonwealth's variant of the Obelisks' signature Aether shielding. Has "
"an integrity of 6 hitpoints, but also boosts standard shield charge rate by "
"20% and grants 50% ion resistance."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17258
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_COMMONWEALTH_SHIELD_DAISY\"]/title"
msgstr "Ionic Shields"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17259
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_COMMONWEALTH_SHIELD_DAISY\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"The Commonwealth's variant of the Obelisks' signature Aether shielding. Has "
"an integrity of 6 hitpoints, but also boosts standard shield charge rate by "
"20% and grants 50% ion resistance."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17267
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_COMMONWEALTH_SHIELD_UNLOCKED\"]/title"
msgstr "Ionic Shields"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17268
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_COMMONWEALTH_SHIELD_UNLOCKED\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"The Commonwealth's variant of the Obelisks' signature Aether shielding. Has "
"an integrity of 6 hitpoints, but also boosts standard shield charge rate by "
"20% and grants 50% ion resistance."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17276
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_COMMONWEALTH_SHIELD_SPECIAL\"]/title"
msgstr "Uplifted Ionic Shields"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17277
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_COMMONWEALTH_SHIELD_SPECIAL\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"The Commonwealth's variant of the Obelisks' signature Aether shielding. Has an integrity of 6 hitpoints, but also boosts standard shield charge rate by 20% and grants 50% ion resistance.\n"
"\n"
"\tThis special version of the augment stacks with other forms of energy shields."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17288
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_AETHER_FORGE\"]/title"
msgstr "Aether Forge"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17289
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_AETHER_FORGE\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"This augment allows you to consume large quantities of resources to create Commonwealth technology. \n"
"\t\n"
"\tThe forge also unleashes nanomachines that eat through boarders, dealing 3 hp/s to all enemy crew onboard."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17299
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_AETHER_FORGE_UNLOCKED\"]/title"
msgstr "Aether Forge"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17300
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_AETHER_FORGE_UNLOCKED\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"This augment allows you to consume large quantities of resources to create Commonwealth technology. \n"
"\t\n"
"\tThe forge also unleashes nanomachines that eat through boarders, dealing 3 hp/s to all enemy crew onboard."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17310
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_ENHANCED_AUGMENTER\"]/title"
msgstr "Enhanced Plating"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17311
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_ENHANCED_AUGMENTER\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"Secret technology of the Enhanced, forged from the knowledge of centuries' worth of consumed Commonwealth tech. Crew can break apart the ship's hull to pay for ship upgrades at empty beacons.\n"
"\t\n"
"\tThe plating also gives the ship full immunity to ion damage, and lowers all scrap gain by 15%."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17321
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_COMMONWEALTH_MAINTENANCE_INFRASTRUCTURE\"]/title"
msgstr "C.M.I. Network"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17322
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_COMMONWEALTH_MAINTENANCE_INFRASTRUCTURE\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"The Commonwealth Maintenance Infrastructure network is an incredibly "
"advanced web of nanomachine-spewing nodes running across the entire ship. It"
" automatically extinguishes fires, repairs breaches, deals 5 hp/s to "
"boarders, and heals your drones and metallic crew by 5 hp/s."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17330
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_LIGHTWEIGHT_COMMONWEALTH_MAINTENANCE_INFRASTRUCTURE\"]/title"
msgstr "Lightweight C.M.I."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17331
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_LIGHTWEIGHT_COMMONWEALTH_MAINTENANCE_INFRASTRUCTURE\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"This version of the Commonwealth Maintenance Infrastructure network is "
"modular enough to be installed onto any ship at the cost of having slightly "
"weaker effects than the original. It automatically extinguishes fires, "
"repairs breaches, deals 2.5 hp/s to boarders, and heals your drones and "
"metallic crew by 2.5 hp/s."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17339
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_COMMONWEALTH_IONIZER\"]/title"
msgstr "Commonwealth Ionizer"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17340
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_COMMONWEALTH_IONIZER\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"An extremely advanced overcharger system that doubles all ion damage dealt "
"by your non-beam weapons and artillery. This augment can't increase the ion "
"damage dealt by any given shot beyond 9."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17349
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_COMMONWEALTH_IONIZER_UNLOCKED\"]/title"
msgstr "Commonwealth Ionizer"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17350
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_COMMONWEALTH_IONIZER_UNLOCKED\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"An extremely advanced overcharger system that doubles all ion damage dealt "
"by your non-beam weapons and artillery. This augment can't increase the ion "
"damage dealt by any given shot beyond 9."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17359
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_COMMONWEALTHS_BODY\"]/title"
msgstr "Commonwealth Corpse"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17360
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_COMMONWEALTHS_BODY\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"The broken, decrepit corpse of an Obelisk, likely belonging to the extinct "
"Commonwealth judging by its grayish hue. Although restoration is not "
"impossible, it will definitely be very, very difficult."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17368
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_WITHERED_PLATING\"]/title"
msgstr "Withered Plating"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17369
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_WITHERED_PLATING\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"This hull plating is composed of an extremely durable, Aether-infused alloy "
"that renders your ship immune to system damage and extremely resistant to "
"sabotage, while also damaging boarders for 1 hp/s. It absorbs scrap to "
"maintain its integrity, reducing scrap gain by 40%."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17377
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_WITHER_PERFECTION\"]/title"
msgstr "Aenwithe's Perfection"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17378
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_WITHER_PERFECTION\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"A number of specialized ship optimizations which provide a set of different benefits.\n"
"\t- 5% faster weapon charge.\n"
"\t- 10% faster shield charge.\n"
"\t- 15% faster FTL Drive charge.\n"
"\t- 15% hull resist chance, 15% system resist chance, and 50% ion resist chance.\n"
"\t- Friendly crew and drones in your ship constantly heal 3 hp/s.\n"
"\t- Enemy crew and drones in your ship constantly take 5 hp/s in damage."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17392
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_WITHER_ENGINEERING\"]/title"
msgstr "Aenwithe's Workstation"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17393
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_WITHER_ENGINEERING\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"This magnificent onboard research laboratory allows its crew to forge "
"cutting-edge technology by spending resources. It also allows the ship to "
"jump to any beacon in the sector for no additional fuel cost."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17401
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_WITHER_SHIELD\"]/title"
msgstr "Aenwithe's Shielding Unit"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17402
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_WITHER_SHIELD\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"A highly advanced energy shield unit with an integrity of 10 hitpoints. It "
"also disables the short-range teleportation of enemy crew."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17410
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_FEDERATION_SYSTEMS\"]/title"
msgstr "Federation Systems"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17411
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_FEDERATION_SYSTEMS\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"An experimental array of systems made specifically for the Federation "
"flagship. It has an energy shield with an integrity of 5 hitpoints that "
"stacks with other super shields as well as the effects of a single copy of "
"Med-Bots, Re-loader and Kernel Greenhouse."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17419
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_ALLIANCE_SYSTEM_PLATING\"]/title"
msgstr "Alliance System Plating"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17420
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_ALLIANCE_SYSTEM_PLATING\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"The upgraded form of the unique technology held by the anti-Coalition. While rather imperfect and flawed, it gets the job done by providing a myriad of unique bonuses.\n"
"\t- A 7 hitpoint energy shield;\n"
"\t- When the hull is damaged, will fire back energy projectiles;\n"
"\t- Empowers crew damage by 30% per Life Support level above 1 power, but applies a 15% combat damage penalty when Life Support is disabled or uninstalled;\n"
"\t- Damages crew vulnerable to Shell gas by 3hp/s;\n"
"\t- Actively puts out fires and seals breaches;\n"
"\t- Adds a death effect to allied crew, making them explode for 15 crew damage against enemies, with a 50% chance to start fires. Stacks upon already existing death effects."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17435
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_CABALS_PROTECTION_ARRAY\"]/title"
msgstr "Cabal's Protection Array"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17436
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_CABALS_PROTECTION_ARRAY\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"An array of supercharged medbots perfectly tuned to keep the ship's crew alive no matter what. While the medbay is powered:\n"
"\t- Your crew will passively heal at 100% the speed of your current level medbay. They also gain a 25% boost to their movement speed for each powered level of medbay;\n"
"\t- At a powered lvl 3 medbay, Totality Commanders gain an extra charge to their Reconstructive Stimulant ability."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17446
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_RUES_ROYAL_PLATING\"]/title"
msgstr "R.U.E.S. Roy. Plating"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17447
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_RUES_ROYAL_PLATING\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"An attempt to fuse every signature augment of the factions that make up the Coalition. As a result, this unique hull armor provides several bonuses.\n"
"\t- 20% hull resist chance. Incoming projectiles that deal 1 damage have a 40% chance to be negated, and all other damage is reduced by 1.\n"
"\t- Automatically repairs breaches on your ship.\n"
"\t- Friendly crew in empty rooms have 35% combat resistance and 50% hazard and stun resistance.\n"
"\t- For each powered level of Life Support, friendly crew gain an additional 25% movement speed, 6.25% maximum health, and reduces active ability cooldowns by 15%.\n"
"\t- Provides an opportunity to ram enemies before combat."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17461
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_ECHO_PLATING\"]/title"
msgstr "E.C.H.O. Plating"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17462
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_ECHO_PLATING\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"The signature technology of E.C.H.O. (Exotic Creatures Hideout  Ordinance). The creator of this plating has chosen to remain anonymous for their own safety. It has several bonuses, including:\n"
"\t- Full ion resistance and 5% chance for systems to resist damage.\n"
"\t- 50% reduction to stun duration on your own ship.\n"
"\t- Increases the maximum number of charges and charges gained per jump for active abilities by 2.\n"
"\t- Allows you to breed two tamed equinoids or non-hatchling Giant Alien Spiders to create a new, untamed equinoid/Giant Alien spider hatchling for free at empty beacons."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17475
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_HOLY_ROCK_PLATING\"]/title"
msgstr "Holy Rock Plating"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17476
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_HOLY_ROCK_PLATING\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"The thickest rock armor ever devised, made specifically for Rockmore's personal cruiser.\n"
"\t- Incoming projectiles that deal 1 damage have a 70% chance to be negated, and all other damage is reduced by 2.\n"
"\t- Provides an opportunity to ram enemies before combat.\n"
"\t- Unfortunately, the plating's weight severely cuts down on the engine's charge time. Your FTL Drive powers up 50% slower."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17488
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_UNITY_SYSTEMS\"]/title"
msgstr "Unity Systems"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17489
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_UNITY_SYSTEMS\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"A refined and augmented array of systems made specifically for the Unity flagship. \n"
"\t\t\n"
"It has an aether shield that stacks with other super shields, Med-Bots at double efficiency, a copy of Re-loader and Shield Charge Booster as well as a stronger Kernel Greenhouse that has an 80% chance to not use ammunition when a missile consuming weapon is fired."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17499
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_SHRAPNEL_AMMO\"]/title"
msgstr "Shrapnel Ammo"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17500
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_SHRAPNEL_AMMO\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"Your crew's ammo was designed specifically to make those hit by it to bleed heavily. Doesn't affect metallic crew.\n"
"\t\t\n"
"Every second, the crew being fought at range by your crew will gain a stack of heavy bleeding, causing them to take damage at a rate of 2 hp/s per stack. Stacks up to 5 times and lasts for 5 seconds."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17510
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_PIRATES_AEGIS\"]/title"
msgstr "Pirate's Aegis"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17511
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_PIRATES_AEGIS\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"This cobbled together piece of aether technology was made by the smartest unaffiliated pirates out there. It has an integrity of 8 hit points. \n"
"\t\t\n"
"While the energy shield is up your weapons and artilleries have +30% accuracy."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17521
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_ZODIAC_AMBUSH\"]/title"
msgstr "Zodiac Ambush"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17522
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_ZODIAC_AMBUSH\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"This piece of technology is what happens when the Syndicate gets their hands on pure aether. It works by replacing the wires between the artillery, weapons, and cloaking systems, allowing surges of power from one to enhance the others.\n"
"\n"
"While you are cloaked, the fire rate of your Weapons and Artillery is improved by 25%."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17532
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_NEO_PANDORA_BOX\"]/title"
msgstr "Neo Pandora's Box"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17533
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_NEO_PANDORA_BOX\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"A mystical square artifact with bright pink lights and a bright white exterior. Unlike their basic counterparts, this strange variation can be opened infinite times and has a much wider range of effects, ranging from internal Automated Re-loader and Automated De-loader to gaining or losing crew, and more.\n"
"\t\t\n"
"It can only, however, be opened 3 times per sector."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17543
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_DRONE_ASCENDER\"]/title"
msgstr "Drone Ascender"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17544
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_DRONE_ASCENDER\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"The fabled 'Drone Booster 2.0', this augment was made by Jon himself after first coming across royal aether tech, using said tech to boost the abilities of crew drones to new levels. Stacks with the effects of Drone Booster.\n"
"\t\t\n"
"Your crew drones gain:\n"
"+20% movement speed;\n"
"+15% boost to combat/sabotage damage, repair/extinguishing speed; \n"
"take 10% less damage; \n"
"break doors twice as quickly; \n"
"provide 1 power in your ship and drain 1 power in the enemy ship;\n"
"+10% boost to crew healing wherever applicable."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17560
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_EGGMANS_VIRUS\"]/title"
msgstr "Eggman's Virus"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17561
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_EGGMANS_VIRUS\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"This unique piece of technology made by the one and only Dr. Ivo Robotnik causes the hacked doors on enemy ships to be thrice as resistant by lowering the enemy's door damage by 66%. \n"
"\t\t\n"
"Your hacking also lasts for 20% longer."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17571
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_REAL_SHIELD\"]/title"
msgstr "R.E.A.L. Defenses"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17572
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_REAL_SHIELD\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"This energy shield unit is composed of a cross between Aether and eldritch "
"technology. It has an integrity of 10 hitpoints, and applies Madness to all "
"enemy crew, even if they are on their own ship."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17580
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_REAL_UTILITIES\"]/title"
msgstr "R.E.A.L. Empowerment"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17581
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_REAL_UTILITIES\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"All allied crew can teleport anywhere on demand, including to the enemy "
"ship, and have immunity to mind control and suffocation."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17589
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_OBSERVER_TECH\"]/title"
msgstr "Observers' Collaboration"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17590
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_OBSERVER_TECH\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"A unique technology network, crafted by the Observers for this vessel, that fuses characteristic technologies of the Separatists, Lost Suns, and Osmians. It provides a number of effects.\n"
"\t- 20% hull resist chance, 100% ion resist chance.\n"
"\t- Automatically extinguishes fires and repairs breaches.\n"
"\t- Friendly crew restore 5 hp/s, gain immunity to being stunned while on your ship, and increase the number of ability charges they have and the charges they restore on jump by 3.\n"
"\t- Enemy crew on your ship take 5 hp/s in damage.\n"
"\t- Provides an opportunity to ram the enemy before combat."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17603
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_OBSERVER_PRESENCE\"]/title"
msgstr "Observers' Presence"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17604
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_OBSERVER_PRESENCE\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"At empty beacons, you can select between gaining the effects of all of "
"Thest's boons, all of Corby's grants, or all of Wakeson's blessings. This "
"effect only considers base Multiverse bonuses, grants rewards from bonuses "
"only once per run, and uses the strongest of multi-leveled bonuses."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17612
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_OBSERVER_BOONS\"]/title"
msgstr "Observer's Boons"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17613
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_OBSERVER_BOONS\"]/desc"
msgstr "Gives the effects of all boons."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17621
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_OBSERVER_BLESSINGS\"]/title"
msgstr "Observer's Blessing"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17622
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_OBSERVER_BLESSINGS\"]/desc"
msgstr "Gives the effects of all blessings."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17630
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_OBSERVER_GRANTS\"]/title"
msgstr "Observer's Grants"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17631
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_OBSERVER_GRANTS\"]/desc"
msgstr "Gives the effects of all grants."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17639
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_SALTED_AIR\"]/title"
msgstr "Saline Air"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17640
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_SALTED_AIR\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"The ship's life support system floods the air with microscopic salt "
"particles. It is very uncomfortable to breathe, and barely able to support "
"most races. Salt people on your ship passively restore 10 hp/s, and enemy "
"Slugs passively take 20 hp/s in damage."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17648
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_SALT_HULL\"]/title"
msgstr "Halite Hull"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17649
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_SALT_HULL\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"The composite hull of the ship contains a large amount of salt crystals, "
"which function as an electrolytic channel for incoming attacks. Your ship is"
" immune to ion damage, and has a 20% chance to resist hull damage."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17657
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_SALT_RELOADER\"]/title"
msgstr "Seasoned Re-loader"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17658
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_SALT_RELOADER\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"A prototype model of automated reloader used exclusively by the Salt Empire."
" It was believed to have died with them, but here in front of you is a "
"working model. It increases the fire rate of all weapons by 50%, but "
"increases your shield cooldown by 90%."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17666
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_OSMIAN_VORTEX\"]/title"
msgstr "Radioactive Black Hole"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17667
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_OSMIAN_VORTEX\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"This ship sources its power from a black hole which emits extreme amounts of"
" radiation. The black hole lowers enemy maximum health, repair, and healing "
"speed depending on your reactor level."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17675
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_OSMIAN_VORTEX_HOLOGRAM\"]/title"
msgstr "Holographic White Hole"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17676
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_OSMIAN_VORTEX_HOLOGRAM\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"This ship sources its power from a white hole which emits extreme amounts of"
" hard light. All allied holograms give double power and their life, damage, "
"repair, movement and sabotage speed scale with reactor levels."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17684
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_OSMIAN_VORTEX_HEAL\"]/title"
msgstr "Healing Anomaly"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17685
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_OSMIAN_VORTEX_HEAL\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"This ship sources its power from a space anomaly which emits extreme amounts"
" of life energy. The vortex boosts the maximum health of all allied crew as "
"well as healing them anywhere constantly, both effects scaling depending on "
"your reactor level."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17693
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_OMNIDRONE_SYSTEM\"]/title"
msgstr "Master of Puppets"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17694
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_OMNIDRONE_SYSTEM\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"This highly advanced drone system, known only by its codename, "
"simultaneously scrambles enemy defense drones and recovers all consumed "
"drones after fights. However, it will only function as long as the Hacking "
"system is operational."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17702
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_BOARDER_DETTERRENT_SYSTEM\"]/title"
msgstr "Anti-Boarder System"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17703
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_BOARDER_DETTERRENT_SYSTEM\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"An advanced variant of the classic emancipation grid. It deals 2 hp/s to "
"boarders, plus an extra 1 hp/s for each level in the Doors system, and "
"reduces their sabotage speed by 70%."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17711
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_RANDOM_AUGMENT_CRATE\"]/title"
msgstr "Gambler's Gift"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17712
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_RANDOM_AUGMENT_CRATE\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"A turquoise box with a navy stripe across its body. Labels on the box claim "
"it \"contains any one useful augment from Multiverse or Forgotten Races\", "
"whatever that means. Come on... you know you want to open it."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17720
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_RANDOM_AUGMENT_CRATE_MULTIVERSE\"]/title"
msgstr "Gambler's Gift [MV]"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17721
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_RANDOM_AUGMENT_CRATE_MULTIVERSE\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"A dark blue box with a star pattern on its lid. Labels on the box claim it "
"\"contains any one useful augment from Multiverse\", whatever that means. "
"Come on... you know you want to open it."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17729
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_FRIEND_MAKER_SHIELD\"]/title"
msgstr "Friend-Maker Shielding"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17730
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_FRIEND_MAKER_SHIELD\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"An energy shield unit crafted as Jerry's latest summer project. It has an "
"integrity of 12 hitpoints, and increases enemy weapon charge time by 10%."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17739
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_TULLY_SHIELD\"]/title"
msgstr "Unified Shielding"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17740
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_TULLY_SHIELD\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"Energy shield technology crafted by the Federation's finest. It has an "
"integrity of 12 hitpoints, reduces the ability cooldowns of friendly crew by"
" 50%, gives their abilities 2 more maximum charges, and causes them to "
"regenerate 2 more ability charges on jump."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17748
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_MFK_TRAINING\"]/title"
msgstr "Ace Training Courses"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17749
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_MFK_TRAINING\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"A shelf of logbooks and training manuals imported from key Rebel "
"strongholds. Allows you to train regular Humans, Medics, and Engineers into "
"Soldiers, and Soldiers and Technicians into MFK Aces, at empty beacons."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17757
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_MFK_EQUIPMENT\"]/title"
msgstr "MFK Arsenal"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17758
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_MFK_EQUIPMENT\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"A crate filled with top-of-the-line weapons and armor. Your humans gain 50 "
"extra maximum health and 100% extra damage in ranged combat."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17766
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_LOCAL_MAINTENANCE\"]/title"
msgstr "Durable Circuitry"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17767
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_LOCAL_MAINTENANCE\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"A high-grade circuitry package for smaller automatons. Drones spawned by "
"Technicians have an infinite lifespan while on your ship."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17775
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_FRIGID_AIR\"]/title"
msgstr "Frigid Air"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17776
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_FRIGID_AIR\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"The interior of your vessel is extremely cold, causing Snowmen to passively "
"heal for 20 hp/s inside your ship and move at double speed. This also allows"
" you to make more Snowmen at empty beacons."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17784
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_SHIPWIDE_HEATER\"]/title"
msgstr "Overdriven Heater"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17785
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_SHIPWIDE_HEATER\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"The interior of your vessel is unbearably hot. This allows slain Lavamen to "
"generate another one upon death. Boarders with a weakness to fire damage "
"also passively take 5 hp/s in damage."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17793
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_SMART_THERMOSTAT\"]/title"
msgstr "Precision Thermostat"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17794
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_SMART_THERMOSTAT\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"A massively over-engineered temperature regulation system that automatically adjusts the climate around each crew to the perfect level.\n"
"\n"
"\tBoth Snowmen and Lavamen passively heal for 20 hp/s while in your ship, and enemy boarders passively take 3 hp/s in damage. Snowmen can now be cloned, move at double speed, and can be built at empty beacons, and Lavamen revive themselves upon death."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17804
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_AI_AVATAR_GENERATOR\"]/title"
msgstr "AI Avatar Generator"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17805
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_AI_AVATAR_GENERATOR\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"A highly sophisticated algorithm-driven machine that can manufacture AI "
"avatars at the cost of some scrap."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17813
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_REBEL_REPLICATOR\"]/title"
msgstr "Rebel Replicator"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17814
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_REBEL_REPLICATOR\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"A marvel of engineering produced by the Rebellion, powered by a hint of "
"Aether. Your weapons will no longer consume missiles, but all of your "
"weapons and artillery have a 20% longer cooldown."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17822
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"REBEL_ID\"]/title"
msgstr "Forged Identification"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17823
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"REBEL_ID\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"A fake Rebel identification card, often used by smugglers to get past security checkpoints. While it's unlikely this will work on high ranking Rebel officers or aggressive vessels who've already identified you as Federation, it should be enough to convince those less certain about your identity, or at least those who aren't very good at their jobs.\n"
"\t\n"
"\tProvides helpful blue options during relevant events."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17832
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_ROYAL_PHEROMONES\"]/title"
msgstr "Royal Pheromones"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17833
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_ROYAL_PHEROMONES\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"A concoction of Mantis pheromones made by the Queen, for the Queen, to be "
"shared with everybody. For each powered level of Life Support, all friendly "
"crew increase their sabotage damage by 20% and their repair speed by 10%. "
"Friendly Hive Mantis also become immune to mind control while Life Support "
"is powered."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17842
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_THICK_EXOSKELETON\"]/title"
msgstr "Thickened Exoskeleton"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17843
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_THICK_EXOSKELETON\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"A small amount of genetic manipulation can do anything in this world, it "
"seems. Your Spider crew take halved damage from hazards, but move 25% "
"slower."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17851
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_GAS_COMPRESSORS\"]/title"
msgstr "Air Compressors"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17852
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_GAS_COMPRESSORS\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"Very crude Old-Earth technology, repurposed for a strange use. Allied Ghost "
"crew gain 20% more maximum health and take up half a crew slot, but move 30%"
" slower."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17860
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_SHIPWIDE_SPEAKERS\"]/title"
msgstr "Omni Sound System"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17861
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_SHIPWIDE_SPEAKERS\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"An advanced speaker system, suitable for a concert venue, that blasts loud, "
"funkalicious music throughout your ship. Allied crew receive a 50% bonus to "
"combat damage and repair speed, and enemy boarders have their combat damage "
"and sabotage speed halved. This effect does not stack with Sammy's music."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17869
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_SLIMER_GEL\"]/title"
msgstr "Slimer's Ectoplasmic Gel"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17870
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_SLIMER_GEL\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"A preternaturally thick blend of Slug breach sealant, only possible to forge using the black magic of Tartarus.\n"
"\n"
"\tCoats the inside of empty rooms. Friendly crew inside of them become immune to hazards, while enemy boarders become unable to fight and move at half speed. The thickness of the gel also instantly closes any breaches in your ship.\n"
"\n"
"\tProvides a cheaper option for repairs at empty beacons."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17883
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_ENDLESS_FEAST\"]/title"
msgstr "Endless Feast"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17884
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_ENDLESS_FEAST\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"The crew in this ship are inflicted with a supernatural hunger for exotic creatures (both friendly and enemy), eating them alive while in the same room as them.\n"
"\n"
"\tNon-exotic crew heal for 10 hp/s and exotic crew lose 5 hp/s while in the same room as each other.\n"
"\n"
"\tThe crew (and all their subtypes) affected are the following: Giant Alien Spiders, Morphs, Six-Legged Equinoids, Tree Lizard Things, Osmian Zoltans and Sirens.\n"
"\n"
"\tLanius can also consume engis and other robotic beings, including drones.\n"
"\n"
"\tBe warned though, Eldritch Beings are inedible and will instead damage your crew by 2 hp/s while being eaten."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17901
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_IONIC_NEBULA_GAS\"]/title"
msgstr "Phys' Ionized Gases"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17902
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_IONIC_NEBULA_GAS\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"This ship is flooded with ionized Shell gas. The gas renders it immune to "
"ion damage, grants friendly crew stun immunity, and damages enemy boarders "
"for 6 hp/s. Drones take doubled damage."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17910
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_STUNNING_GAS_SUIT\"]/title"
msgstr "Stunning Gas Suit"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17911
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_STUNNING_GAS_SUIT\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"Your crew is wearing a suit that surrounds them with a cloud that can force even the sturdiest Rockman to be stunned.\n"
"\n"
"Enemy crew in the same room as your crew will be stunned for at least 2x the normal amount. \n"
"\t\n"
"Friendly crew are stunned for at most 0.5x the normal amount. (Crew 'immune' to stun are unaffected)"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17924
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_CHROMATIC_GAS\"]/title"
msgstr "Chromatic Gas"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17925
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_CHROMATIC_GAS\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"The perfected formula which combines the signature abilities of all Shell gases. The gas:\n"
"\n"
"-Greatly harms all hostile crew as well as drones on your ship at a rate of 12hp/s;\n"
"-Mimics the effects of the Medbay all around the ship, healing friendly crew at 3.2 hp/s;\n"
"-Actively puts out fires and seals breaches;\n"
"-Gives 50% resistance to ion damage and grants friendly crew 50% stun resistance;\n"
"-Makes friendly crew take 0.8x damage and slows enemy crew's movement speed by 0.9x."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17940
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_GHOSTLY_PHEROMONES\"]/title"
msgstr "Aleenor's Pheromones"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17941
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_GHOSTLY_PHEROMONES\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"A potent, one-of-a-kind pheromone concoction fills the ship. The mix grants increasingly strong bonuses to crew for each powered level of Life Support.\n"
"\t- 1 power: Friendly crew gain immunity to suffocation.\n"
"\t- 2 power: Friendly crew gain the ability to phase through doors.\n"
"\t- 3 power: Friendly crew gain the ability to teleport to any room on your ship.\n"
"\t- 4 power: Friendly crew gain the ability to teleport to and from any room on either ship."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17953
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_MOLTEN_ARMOR\"]/title"
msgstr "Vin's Molten Armor"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17954
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_MOLTEN_ARMOR\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"The ship is flooded with real, obscenely hot lava. This hostile environment passively deals 15 hp/s to both allied and enemy crew. This damage counts as fire damage, and is modified accordingly.\n"
"\t\n"
"\tThe plating itself has a 25% chance to resist any hull damage, provides an opportunity to ram the enemy ship before combat and incoming projectiles that deal 1 damage have a 20% chance to be negated, and all other damage is reduced by 1."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17965
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_PROPHETS_BLESSING\"]/title"
msgstr "Prophet's Blessing"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17966
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_PROPHETS_BLESSING\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"The True Prophet's blessing flows through the veins of each and every one of your crew like poison flows through blood. Gives crew damage and sabotage speed to your crew depending on how many fires are in the same room as them.\n"
"\t- 1 Fire: Friendly crew deal 1.25x damage and sabotage 1.15x faster.\n"
"\t- 2 Fires: Friendly crew deal 1.5x damage and sabotage 1.3x faster.\n"
"\t- 3 Fires: Friendly crew deal 2x damage and sabotage 1.6x faster.\n"
"\t- 4 Fires: Friendly crew deal 2.5x damage and sabotage 2x faster.\n"
"\t- 5+ Fires: Friendly crew deal 3.5x damage and sabotage 3x faster."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17980
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_ENERGY_SIPHON\"]/title"
msgstr "Cleo's Energy Siphon"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17981
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_ENERGY_SIPHON\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"Your crew can siphon energy from drones. For each crew drone you control, "
"your crew gains +0.25x damage and repair as well as +25 max health. Crew "
"drones fired by your weapons and artilleries also count towards this number."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17989
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_HOLY_FURY\"]/title"
msgstr "Zulu's Holy Conviction"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17990
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_HOLY_FURY\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"The ship and its weaponry are imbued by a divine force. Friendly crew heal "
"and clone 50% faster, and beam weapons pierce 2 additional shield layers."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17998
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_RADIOACTIVE_FURY_C\"]/title"
msgstr "Radioactive Fury [C]"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:17999
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_RADIOACTIVE_FURY_C\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"Can swap between its crew centric mode and its shipboard centric mode before combat. CURRENT MODE: CREW\n"
"\n"
"While in Crew mode: Your crew heal 200% and clone 100% faster and are immune to hazards.\n"
"\n"
"While in Shipboard mode: Your weapons pierce 2 extra layers of shields and your shields recharge 50% faster."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18011
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_RADIOACTIVE_FURY_S\"]/title"
msgstr "Radioactive Fury [S]"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18012
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_RADIOACTIVE_FURY_S\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"Can swap between its crew centric mode and its shipboard centric mode before combat. CURRENT MODE: SHIPBOARD\n"
"\n"
"While in Crew mode: Your crew heal 200% and clone 100% faster and are immune to hazards.\n"
"\n"
"While in Shipboard mode: Your weapons pierce 2 extra layers of shields and your shields recharge 50% faster."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18024
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_NECROMANCER_SHIELD\"]/title"
msgstr "G's Magical Shield"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18025
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_NECROMANCER_SHIELD\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"An absurdly powerful energy shield unit. Has an integrity of no less than 80"
" points, and offers the ability to jam an enemy's bypass unit before battle "
"if they have one."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18033
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_NECROMANCER_SHIELD_B\"]/title"
msgstr "G's Magical Shield"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18034
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_NECROMANCER_SHIELD_B\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"An absurdly powerful energy shield unit. Has an integrity of no less than 80"
" points, and offers the ability to jam an enemy's bypass unit before battle "
"if they have one."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18042
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_NECROMANCER_SHIELD_C\"]/title"
msgstr "G's Perfect Shield"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18043
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_NECROMANCER_SHIELD_C\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"A modified shield made by G under Y's supervision and with Aenwithe's help. "
"Has an integrity of 30 points, grants immunity to ion damage and boosts "
"standard shield charge rate by 100%"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18051
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_GS_PERFECT_GRID\"]/title"
msgstr "G's Perfect Grid"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18052
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_GS_PERFECT_GRID\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"Built by G herself, this modified Emancipation Grid will kill and extract "
"the soul of any non-undead, Obelisk or Cognitive crew (friend or foe) that "
"steps into the ship. In their place, a specter will be summoned that uses no"
" crew slots."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18060
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_NECROMANCER_SHIELD_CURSED\"]/title"
msgstr "G's Cursed Shield"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18061
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_NECROMANCER_SHIELD_CURSED\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"An absurdly powerful energy shield unit. Has an integrity of no less than 80"
" points, and offers the ability to jam an enemy's bypass unit before battle "
"if they have one. Also gives your ship a 50% chance to resist ion damage."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18069
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_NECROMANTIC_PROJECTION\"]/title"
msgstr "G's Necromantic Aura"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18070
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_NECROMANTIC_PROJECTION\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"A powerful spell blankets this ship, granting all allied Specter crew 100 "
"extra maximum health and immunity to mind control."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18078
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_NECROMANTIC_PROJECTION_CURSED\"]/title"
msgstr "G's Cursed Aura"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18079
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_NECROMANTIC_PROJECTION_CURSED\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"A powerful spell blankets this ship, granting all allied Specter crew 200 "
"extra maximum health and immunity to mind control."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18087
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_AETHER_NECRONOMICON\"]/title"
msgstr "Aetheric Necronomicon"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18088
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_AETHER_NECRONOMICON\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"A tome, crafted with the finest Aether-infused materials, containing the "
"knowledge needed to perform unspeakable acts of black magic. All allied crew"
" killed aboard this ship return to life as a Specter, in addition to being "
"cloned if possible. Specters can't be resurrected by this augment. "
"Additionally, crew clone 100% faster."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18096
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_AETHER_NECRONOMICON_ENEMY\"]/title"
msgstr "Aether Necronomicon (Enemy)"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18097
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_AETHER_NECRONOMICON_ENEMY\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"A tome, crafted with the finest Aether-infused materials, containing the "
"knowledge needed to perform unspeakable acts of black magic. All allied "
"Revenant crew killed aboard this ship return to life as a Specter, in "
"addition to being cloned if possible. Specters can't be resurrected by this "
"augment. Additionally, crew clone 100% faster."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18105
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_CHAOTIC_NECRONOMICON\"]/title"
msgstr "Chaotic Necronomicon"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18106
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_CHAOTIC_NECRONOMICON\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"A tome whose pages are full of mesmerizing static and cognito-hazardous "
"symbols, driving all who attempt to parse it to madness. All allied crew "
"killed aboard this ship return to life as a Siren, in addition to being "
"cloned if possible. Sirens can't be resurrected by this augment."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18114
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_FROZEN_CRYSTAL_ARMOR\"]/title"
msgstr "Frostwall's Frozen Armor"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18115
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_FROZEN_CRYSTAL_ARMOR\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"Sleek, frigid hull plating composed of a Crystalline base, ectoplasm, and a small amount of pure entropy. When this ship takes damage, it launches a crystal shard that deals 1 damage, locks down rooms, pierces 2 shields and is invisible to most defense drones.\n"
"\n"
"\tThe plating itself also grants a 50% system resist chance."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18125
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_FROZEN_CRYSTAL_ARMOR_ENEMY\"]/title"
msgstr "Frostwall's Frozen Armor (Enemy)"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18126
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_FROZEN_CRYSTAL_ARMOR_ENEMY\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"Sleek, frigid hull plating composed of a Crystalline base, ectoplasm, and a small amount of pure entropy. When this ship takes damage, it launches a crystal shard that deals 1 damage, locks down rooms, pierces 2 shields and is invisible to most defense drones.\n"
"\n"
"\tThe plating itself also grants a 50% system resist chance."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18136
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_TIIIKAKA_MEMBERSHIP\"]/title"
msgstr "Tiiikaka Membership"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18137
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_TIIIKAKA_MEMBERSHIP\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"An official blank customer membership card for the Tiiikaka clan. When registered on the storage menu it will be consumed and instantly raise your slaver reputation to 10. This method is thankfully one which the Federation didn't catch on to yet, so it won't harm your standing with them.\n"
"\n"
"Once consumed will also allow you to find a single slaver ship during jumpspeed."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18147
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_DEATHLY_SPORES\"]/title"
msgstr "Deathbloom Spores"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18148
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_DEATHLY_SPORES\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"A highly mutated strain of Vampweed spores which causes enemies who die to "
"make other enemy crew take 10% more damage and increases their ability "
"cooldown by 10%. This effect stacks and applies across all ships."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18156
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_DEATHLY_GAS\"]/title"
msgstr "Deathbloom Gas"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18157
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_DEATHLY_GAS\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"A highly concentrated gas made out of Deathbloom's spores. Causes enemies "
"who died after stepping inside your ship to make other enemy crew take 25% "
"more damage and increases their ability cooldown by 25%."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18165
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_LIFEBLOOD_ENERGY\"]/title"
msgstr "Lifeblood Energy"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18166
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_LIFEBLOOD_ENERGY\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"A specialized machine that turns the lifeforce of dead crew into energy "
"shield hitpoints. When any crew dies your energy shield recharges 2 "
"hitpoints which can't exceed the max energy shield count. Also comes with a "
"built in energy shield unit with an integrity of 5 hitpoints. Works on crew "
"across all ships."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18174
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_LIVING_SHIP\"]/title"
msgstr "Living Vessel"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18175
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_LIVING_SHIP\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"This ship is a single, large, Morph-like living organism, able to consume "
"crew at empty beacons to bolster its own properties. Crew sacrificed to the "
"ship can't be cloned."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18183
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_TELEPORT_RECALL\"]/title"
msgstr "Personal Teleporters"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18184
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_TELEPORT_RECALL\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"Crew on an enemy ship that is jumping or being destroyed will be "
"automatically recalled."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18191
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_SOUL_STEALER\"]/title"
msgstr "Soul Stealer"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18192
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_SOUL_STEALER\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"This ship lost the ability to eat generic crew for boosts, but in its place it can now absorb the very souls of notable beings. This power, however, won't work on Obelisk/undead/chaotic/Morph crew or those found in the center of everything.\n"
"\n"
"Crew sacrificed to the ship can't be cloned."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18202
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_GHOSTLY_REPAIR_BOTS\"]/title"
msgstr "Charror's Nanomachines"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18203
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_GHOSTLY_REPAIR_BOTS\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"Charror's experiments with nanomachines have allowed them to infuse Med-Bots with souls. The nanomachines passively repair systems and extinguish fires at the same rate as a human, multiplied by the amount of powered system levels in Drone Control. \n"
"\t\t\n"
"They also seal breaches at a static rate."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18214
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_THE_ORACLE\"]/title"
msgstr "The Oracle"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18215
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_THE_ORACLE\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle"
" The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The "
"Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The"
" Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle "
"The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle"
" The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The "
"Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The"
" Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle "
"The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle"
" The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The "
"Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The"
" Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle "
"The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle"
" The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The "
"Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle The Oracle"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18224
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_GLITCHED_LUNGS\"]/title"
msgstr "Glitched Lungs"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18225
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_GLITCHED_LUNGS\"]/desc"
msgstr "Your crew are immune to suffocation while in your ship."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18234
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_DISCHARGE_SURGE\"]/title"
msgstr "Leo's Absorption Burst"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18235
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_DISCHARGE_SURGE\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"The engines on this ship are able to absorb energy from the enemy ship, "
"allowing you to downgrade the enemy's systems before combat to a degree "
"determined by your engine level. Using this effect will also cripple your "
"own engines, so be wary!"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18244
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_AETHER_NAVIGATION_SYSTEM\"]/title"
msgstr "Aether Navigation System"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18245
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_AETHER_NAVIGATION_SYSTEM\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"The ship's navigation systems are all made out of aether, with capabilities unseen in most ships.\n"
"\n"
"Allows you to jump to any beacon, regardless of if it has been visited before for 2 fuel, with visited beacons only costing 1 fuel; \n"
"\n"
"Reveals details about surrounding beacons, and allows you to see up to 2 sectors ahead in the sector map, even if said sectors aren't adjacent to the current one."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18258
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_MALWARE_OS\"]/title"
msgstr "Malware OS"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18259
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_MALWARE_OS\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"The ship's systems are all made from the ground up to thrive when the ship's hacking system is active. While you are hacking an enemy room, your weapons charge at 1.5x speed, your shields recharge at 2x speed and your ship gains +5 dodge.\n"
"\n"
"If your hacking system has 3 power in it, then your crew will also deal +0.25x damage and move at +0.5x speed."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18270
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_ENERGY_SHIELD_BATTERY\"]/title"
msgstr "Searak's Shield Adapter"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18271
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_ENERGY_SHIELD_BATTERY\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"This revolutionary piece of technology allows you to generate layers of energy shielding passively, up to a maximum amount determined by your shield level. \n"
"\t\t\n"
"\tThe speed of which the layers regenerate scales with shield recharge levels and the skill that your crew mans shields with.\n"
"\t\t\n"
"\tThe adapter is very power-intensive, halving the recharge rate of your regular shields."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18284
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_ENERGY_SHIELD_BATTERY_ENEMY\"]/title"
msgstr "Searak's Shield Adapter (Enemy)"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18285
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_ENERGY_SHIELD_BATTERY_ENEMY\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"This revolutionary piece of technology allows you to generate layers of "
"energy shielding passively, up to a maximum amount determined by your shield"
" level. The adapter is very power-intensive, halving the recharge rate of "
"your regular shields."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18294
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_SELF_AWARE_COGNITIVE_INTELLIGENCE\"]/title"
msgstr "S.A.C.I"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18295
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_SELF_AWARE_COGNITIVE_INTELLIGENCE\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"The Self Aware Cognitive Intelligence (S.A.C.I) is one of the most advanced "
"AI modules ever created, and largely untested. Ships with the module "
"installed automatically man all of their systems at skill level 2. Also "
"grants manual control of artilleries with no downsides."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18304
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_ANNIHILATION_GRID\"]/title"
msgstr "Annihilation Grid"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18305
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_ANNIHILATION_GRID\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"An extremely advanced emancipation grid created by the Legionnaires, using "
"Aether to enhance its normal capabilities, though its effects haven't been "
"able to be tested extensively. Enemy boarders passively lose 10 hp/s, lose "
"the ability to phase through doors or move by teleporting, and deal halved "
"damage to doors."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18313
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_ANNIHILATION_GRID_UNLOCKED\"]/title"
msgstr "Annihilation Grid"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18314
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_ANNIHILATION_GRID_UNLOCKED\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"An extremely advanced emancipation grid created by the Legionnaires, using "
"Aether to enhance its normal capabilities. Enemy boarders passively lose 10 "
"hp/s, lose the ability to phase through doors or move by teleporting, and "
"deal halved damage to doors."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18322
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_ZOLTAN_ENERGY_GRID\"]/title"
msgstr "Ministry Prototype Grid"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18323
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_ZOLTAN_ENERGY_GRID\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"An experimental emancipation grid forged by the Ministry using hard-light "
"technology. Enemy boarders passively lose 4 hp/s, plus 2 hp/s for every "
"level in the Doors system beyond the first. Boarders who die on your ship "
"fully repair the system they are standing in, overwriting any death effect "
"they normally have."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18331
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_ENERGY_HULL\"]/title"
msgstr "Hard-Light Hull"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18332
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_ENERGY_HULL\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"A clandestine research operation by the Ministry resulted in hull plating "
"directly infused with hard light technology. This ship's hull health is "
"always equal to the integrity of its energy shield."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18340
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_FEDERATION_OVERCLOCKED_GRID\"]/title"
msgstr "Expurgation Grid"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18341
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_FEDERATION_OVERCLOCKED_GRID\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"A customized emancipation grid made by the Federation, pushed to its "
"absolute limit by its constructors. Enemies who board your ship passively "
"lose 15 hp/s, and drones and mechanical crew are killed instantly if they "
"try to board you."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18349
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_OVERCLOKED_SYSTEMS\"]/title"
msgstr "Overclocked Systems"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18350
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_OVERCLOKED_SYSTEMS\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"This ship's systems are overtuned beyond their normal limits, and certainly "
"past Federation regulations. Your Cloaking, Hacking, Mind Control, and "
"Temporal Manipulator systems have their cooldown reduced by 5 seconds."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18358
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_EDUTAINMENT_MODULE\"]/title"
msgstr "Edutainment Module"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18359
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_EDUTAINMENT_MODULE\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"This newest version of \"Callie's Fun Mathematical Questions\" can be activated before a fight to test your knowledge on math. \n"
"\n"
"Every 15 seconds you will be asked a question, get it right and the enemy ship will suffer one of several penalties, answer it wrong and you will be punished instead."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18370
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_STATIC\"]/title"
msgstr "Field of Static"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18371
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_STATIC\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"This ship's interior is completely filled with mesmerizing static and "
"maddening whispers. Enemy boarders will freeze in place, entranced by the "
"horrifying interior until removed from the ship."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18379
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_WATCHER_SHIELD\"]/title"
msgstr "Watcher's Protection"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18380
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_WATCHER_SHIELD\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"An energy shield infused with esoteric, powerful chaos. It has an integrity "
"of 15 hit points, grants your ship a 50% chance to take no damage from non-"
"ion damage, and functions as an energy shield bypass unit."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18388
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_WATCHER_SHIELD_B\"]/title"
msgstr "Watcher's Protection"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18389
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_WATCHER_SHIELD_B\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"An energy shield infused with esoteric, powerful chaos. It has an integrity "
"of 15 hit points, grants your ship a 50% chance to take no damage from non-"
"ion damage, and functions as an energy shield bypass unit."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18397
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_WATCHER_SHIELD_C\"]/title"
msgstr "Watcher's Protection"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18398
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_WATCHER_SHIELD_C\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"An energy shield infused with esoteric, powerful chaos. It has an integrity "
"of 15 hit points, grants your ship a 50% chance to take no damage from non-"
"ion damage, and functions as an energy shield bypass unit."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18406
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_PSIONIC_HELMETS\"]/title"
msgstr "Psionic Helmets"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18407
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_PSIONIC_HELMETS\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"The crew in this ship are equipped with unique helmets made by the Watcher themselves, giving them a taste of a siren's psionic prowess.\n"
"\n"
"As long as any enemy crew is mind controlled, your non-Siren crew drain enemy crew in the same room as them for 5hp/s. Also prevents non-Rhyme enemy crew from teleporting."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18418
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_SIREN_LEECH\"]/title"
msgstr "Spirit Leech"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18419
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_SIREN_LEECH\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"A powerful force within your vessel allows allied Siren crew to recover "
"health equal to the passive damage they deal. In exchange, their passive "
"damage is halved."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18427
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_HER_BLESSING\"]/title"
msgstr "Her Blessing"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18428
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_HER_BLESSING\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"Your crew have been blessed by a flicker of Her power. They can all slightly"
" heal instead of suffocating."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18436
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_LEGION_AEGIS\"]/title"
msgstr "Legionnaire's Aegis"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18437
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_LEGION_AEGIS\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"This incredibly powerful energy shield was forged by the Rebels' best technicians and installed on a secret Flagship project led by Vance-1. It has an integrity of 10 hit points. While the energy shield is up:\n"
"\n"
"- The fire rate of your Weapons and Artillery is improved by 20%;\n"
"- Your ship's evasion is increased by 10;\n"
"- The ship's FTL Drive powers up 60% faster."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18449
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_LEGION_SPIRIT\"]/title"
msgstr "Spirit of the Rebellion"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18450
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_LEGION_SPIRIT\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"The ship's atmosphere fosters absolute dedication to the Rebel cause, "
"including the oppression of dissidents. Your Human crew are considered to "
"have all of their basic crew labs; this effect stacks with the actual crew "
"labs. Your non-Human crew are unable to healed or be cloned."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18458
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_SUPREME_HATRED\"]/title"
msgstr "Supreme Hatred"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18459
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_SUPREME_HATRED\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"The crew hired for this ship were specifically picked to be as hateful and prone to violence as possible. Every faction with the ability to gain notoriety or lose reputation will give different run-permanent bonuses after reaching either +3 notoriety or -3 reputation.\n"
"\n"
"Those bonuses need to be claimed in the storage check menu and will not vanish if your notoriety went under 2 or reputation rose to above -2. Check the storage check option to see what all the effects are."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18469
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_GOLDEN_SYSTEMS\"]/title"
msgstr "Gilded Circuitry"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18470
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_GOLDEN_SYSTEMS\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"Your ship is literally powered by the presence of scrap. The more scrap you have aboard at any given moment, the more efficient your ship's components run.\n"
"\t- For every 10 scrap in your cargo, your weapons charge 1% faster.\n"
"\t- For every 5 scrap in your cargo, your shields regenerate 1% faster.\n"
"\t- For every 2 scrap in your cargo, your FTL Drive charges 1% faster."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18482
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_GOLDEN_SYSTEMS_ENEMY\"]/title"
msgstr "Gilded Circuitry (Enemy)"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18483
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_GOLDEN_SYSTEMS_ENEMY\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"Your ship is literally powered by the presence of scrap. The more scrap you have aboard at any given moment, the more efficient your ship's components run.\n"
"\t- For every 10 scrap in your cargo, your weapons charge 1% faster.\n"
"\t- For every 5 scrap in your cargo, your shields regenerate 1% faster.\n"
"\t- For every 2 scrap in your cargo, your FTL Drive charges 1% faster."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18495
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_SILVER_SYSTEMS\"]/title"
msgstr "Silver Circuitry"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18496
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_SILVER_SYSTEMS\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"Your ship is protected by the presence of scrap. The more scrap you have aboard at any given moment, the higher your defenses will be.\n"
"\t- For every 20 scrap in your cargo, you have +1% chance to negate incoming hull damage.\n"
"\t- For every 30 scrap in your cargo, you have +1% chance to negate incoming system damage."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18507
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_INFESTATION\"]/title"
msgstr "Spider Infestation"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18508
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_INFESTATION\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"Every 15 seconds, a friendly but uncontrollable spider will violently burst "
"out of enemy crew, dealing 5 damage to them. These spiders will die after 7 "
"seconds. This effect applies on both ships."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18516
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_INFESTATION_ENEMY\"]/title"
msgstr "Spider Infestation (Enemy)"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18517
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_INFESTATION_ENEMY\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"Every 25 seconds, a friendly but uncontrollable spider will violently burst "
"out of enemy crew. Such spiders deal halved combat damage, and will die "
"after 5 seconds. This effect applies on both ships."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18525
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_DOMESTICATION\"]/title"
msgstr "Domestication"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18526
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_DOMESTICATION\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"Your uncontrollable non-robotic alien crew are controllable when in the same"
" ship as a friendly human crew."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18534
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_CLOAK_OF_DARKNESS\"]/title"
msgstr "Cloak of Darkness"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18535
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_CLOAK_OF_DARKNESS\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"The ship's hull is shrouded in an ethereal shadow. Incoming projectiles have"
" a 25% chance to be completely nullified, either missing outright or simply "
"dealing no damage."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18543
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_ANGELIC_SHIELD\"]/title"
msgstr "Angelic Shield"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18544
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_ANGELIC_SHIELD\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"The ship's hull is blessed by divine forces. Enemy weapons have -20% "
"accuracy and enemy weapons and drones pierce 2 less shield layers."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18552
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_SHADOW_MIST\"]/title"
msgstr "Shadow Mist"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18553
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_SHADOW_MIST\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"Your crew have sold their souls to be on this ship, granting them extreme power, at a cost. All your crew become invisible to enemy crew for as long as there isn't a drone in the same room as them. \n"
"\t\t\n"
"However, the cost is equally as horrific. Your crew's health is set to 10 and cannot be increased in any way.\n"
"\n"
"Eldritch and robot crew aren't affected by this augment."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18565
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_PANIC_ATTACK\"]/title"
msgstr "Panic Attacks"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18566
msgid "data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_PANIC_ATTACK\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"Something about the atmosphere of this vessel puts everyone on edge. All of "
"your Equinoids now take normal damage from fire, and deal doubled combat "
"damage while in a room that is on fire."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18574
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_MADDENING_PRESENCE\"]/title"
msgstr "Maddening Presence"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18575
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_MADDENING_PRESENCE\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"The walls within this ship seem to shift and twist around you with every "
"step you take. Allied Thing crew deal 50% more combat damage and move twice "
"as fast, but allied non-Thing crew are permanently inflicted with Madness."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18583
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_FORBIDDEN_DESIGN\"]/title"
msgstr "Forbidden Design"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18584
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_FORBIDDEN_DESIGN\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"This ship is constructed with horrific eldritch technology lining the halls. It emits waves of shaped chaotic energy that inflict Blasphemy, causing all enemy crew and drones to lose their death effects.\n"
"\t\t\t\t\n"
"The technology also functions as an energy shield with an integrity of 12 hit points, and creates random bonuses that occur when the ship takes hull damage."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18594
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_FORBIDDEN_DESIGN_SHIELD\"]/title"
msgstr "Forbidden Design"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18595
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_FORBIDDEN_DESIGN_SHIELD\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"This ship is constructed with horrific eldritch technology lining the halls. It emits waves of shaped chaotic energy that inflict Blasphemy, causing all enemy crew and drones to lose their death effects.\n"
"\t\t\n"
"The technology also functions as an energy shield with an integrity of 12 hit points, and creates random bonuses that occur when the ship takes hull damage."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18605
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_SLOWFUL_MASTERY\"]/title"
msgstr "Slowful Mastery"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18606
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_SLOWFUL_MASTERY\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"This ship has mastered one aspect of the Temporal Manipulator system, its "
"slowness side. While your Temporal Manipulator system is powered to at least"
" lvl 3, your enemy's weapons recharge 15% slower and their shields recharge "
"30% slower."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18614
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_SIREN_CALL_BEACON\"]/title"
msgstr "Siren Call Beacon"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18615
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_SIREN_CALL_BEACON\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"A hidden beacon in this ship scrambles the mind of enemy crew, stripping them of any mind control resistance and doubling how long they are stunned for. \n"
"\t\t\n"
"The beacon also houses a small energy reserve for your Mind Control system, allowing it to be ready 5 seconds faster."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18625
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_NEXUS_TECH_SCHEMATICS\"]/title"
msgstr "Nexus-Tech Schematics"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18626
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_NEXUS_TECH_SCHEMATICS\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"Nestled within this ship's database are blueprints for extremely powerful "
"and extremely expensive internal upgrades, custom-tailored for the vessel."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18634
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_NEXUS_ARM_ELECTROMAGNETIC\"]/title"
msgstr "Electromagnetic Arm"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18635
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_NEXUS_ARM_ELECTROMAGNETIC\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"Before combat, you can activate this arm to lower the enemy's accuracy by "
"10% at the cost of losing your sensors."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18642
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_NEXUS_ARM_WEAPON\"]/title"
msgstr "Weapon Dismemberment Arm"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18643
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_NEXUS_ARM_WEAPON\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"Before combat, you can activate this arm to remove one of the enemy's "
"weapons at the cost of 8 reactor power. Also has a 10% chance to grant 10 "
"scrap for each power bar the disabled weapon requires."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18650
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_NEXUS_ARM_MISSILE\"]/title"
msgstr "Missile Recovery Arm"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18651
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_NEXUS_ARM_MISSILE\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"Missed shots from weapons that consume ammunition will refund 1 missile."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18658
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_NEXUS_ARM_SHIP\"]/title"
msgstr "Ship-Part Recovery Arm"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18659
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_NEXUS_ARM_SHIP\"]/desc"
msgstr "Taking hull damage gives you 0-2 scrap."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18666
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_NEXUS_PILOT_RAM\"]/title"
msgstr "Incisive Ramming Upgrade"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18667
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_NEXUS_PILOT_RAM\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"Before combat, you can choose a system to ram. You will deal 2 damage to the"
" enemy hull and the chosen system, breaching it. The impact will also deal 1"
" damage to your own hull and to your corresponding system. Bypasses "
"resistances."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18674
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_NEXUS_PILOT_AUTOMAN_1\"]/title"
msgstr "Enhanced Auto-Piloting LvL 1 Upgrade"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18675
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_NEXUS_PILOT_AUTOMAN_1\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"All of your systems will be automatically manned at least at level 1 skill."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18683
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_NEXUS_PILOT_AUTOMAN_2\"]/title"
msgstr "Enhanced Auto-Piloting LvL 2 Upgrade"

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18684
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_NEXUS_PILOT_AUTOMAN_2\"]/desc"
msgstr ""
"All of your systems will be automatically manned at least at level 2 skill."

#: src-en/data/blueprints.xml.append:18692
msgid ""
"data/blueprints.xml.append$//augBlueprint[@name=\"FR_NEXUS_PILOT_IMMUNITY\"]/title"
